law.text:
Bonds issued under this subtitle shall:
Be dated;
Bear interest at the rate or rates that the sanitary commission determines;
Bear the seal of the district;
Be signed for the district;
Bear maturity dates that:
Are determined by the sanitary commission; and
Are not more than 40 years from the date of issue; and
Subject to the limitation on liability of each member county of a multiple county district under § 9-696 of this subtitle, be endorsed by each member county as follows: "The payment of interest when due and the principal at maturity is guaranteed by .......... (name of member county), Maryland".
